<item>
            <title>[LU-9974] Need a lustre client for centos 6.4 for our lustre install at Roswell Park Cancer Institute </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9974</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
The Intel Lustre version we are using expects Centos 6.5 or later on the client (compute) side. We are at Centos 6.4 due to the Ibrix client not being supported on versions above that. We can get Intel to compile a Lustre client for Centos 6.4, but since this is not their standard build, they are requesting that Roswell (end customer) open an Intel JIRA ticket to request this specific version.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
